description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing date: 11th November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Northumbria Healthcare NHS Foundation Trust is urgently seeking to appoint physicians associates for a period of 3 to 6 months. The posts will support the opening of an Acute Orthopaedic ward at the Northumbria Specialist Emergency Care Hospital (The Northumbria) over the winter period.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The posts will help to provide day to day cover primarily for Trauma and Orthopaedic patients. They will provide routine peri-operative care, dealing with acute emergencies and general medical care of these patients. The post will involve working constructively with the orthogeriatric team to provide holistic care for trauma patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The following define the theoretical, practical, professional and specialist knowledge required for the post:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Accredited Physician Associate training programme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Passed national final examination in the UK&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Teaching experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evidence of continuing professional development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding of safeguarding adults and patients with a learning disability&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience of working in an ambulatory care unit, surgical wards or emergency department&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Desirable&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advanced Life Support&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Teaching qualification&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mr Iain McCallum, Deputy Business Unit Director&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;iain.mccallum@northumbria-healthcare.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
